Premium Page Blobs are designed for random read/write operations and are primarily used for Azure Virtual Machine disks.

They are backed by SSD storage and provide consistent low-latency performance.

For example, OS disks and data disks for VMs are stored as page blobs.

A real-life use case is running high-performance databases on VMs.

Another example is enterprise applications requiring fast disk access.

Premium page blobs ensure stable and predictable performance for disk-intensive workloads.
